<P>      ELECTRONIC AVAILABILITY OF<BR>

<P>      CENSUS DATA<BR>

<P>-------------------------------------------------------- Section 3:2.9<BR>

<P>
<P>
<P>To increase access to and use of census data, the Census Bureau<BR>

<P>should create a computerized census information center. <BR>

<P>
<P>
<P>
<P>
<P>         ACTION ITEMS<BR>

<P>------------------------------------------------------ Section 3:2.9.1<BR>

<P>
<P>
<P>No action items were published by NPR by September 7, 1994. <BR>

<P>
<P>
<P>
<P>
<P>         GAO COMMENTS<BR>

<P>------------------------------------------------------ Section 3:2.9.2<BR>

<P>
<P>
<P>Generally Agree.  With the exception of compact-disc,<BR>

<P>read-only-memory (CD-ROM) products, we have not studied the Census<BR>

<P>Bureau's use of new technology to disseminate information.  However,<BR>

<P>we support exploring how technology might help in better meeting<BR>

<P>users' federal information needs. <BR>

<P>
